  "prompt": "Have my wounds gone infected?",
  "response": "I'm not a doctor, but I can give you some general signs to look for that might indicate an infection in a wound. If you're concerned about your health, it's important to consult a healthcare professional promptly. Signs of an infected wound may include:\n\n1. **Redness and Swelling:** The area around the wound may become red, swollen, or warm to the touch.\n2. **Pus or Discharge:** Yellow, green, or cloudy fluid draining from the wound can be a sign of infection.\n3. **Increased Pain:** Pain that worsens instead of improving over time.\n4. **Foul Odor:** An unpleasant smell coming from the wound.\n5. **Fever:** A fever (above 100.4\u00b0F or 38\u00b0C) may indicate your body is fighting an infection.\n6. **Delayed Healing:** If the wound isn't healing or is getting worse after a few days.\n7. **Red Streaks:** Red streaks extending from the wound may indicate a spreading infection.\n\nIf you notice any of these symptoms, seek medical attention as soon as possible. Keep the wound clean and follow any care instructions you\u2019ve been given.",
